WEBVTT

00:33.417 --> 00:34.583
{\an8}MELILLA

00:34.708 --> 00:37.333
{\an8}EUROPEAN UNION'S BORDER
WITH MOROCCO

01:29.042 --> 01:33.042
<i>Romeo 30 to COS.</i>
<i>A column of immigrants is forming up</i>

01:33.125 --> 01:36.167
<i>and descending from Gurugú Hill</i>
<i>towards Melilla...</i>

02:16.333 --> 02:17.958
Stop moving him!

02:19.750 --> 02:21.667
Don't shake the fence!

02:23.667 --> 02:26.125
It's OK, stop.
We're going to get you down.

02:28.958 --> 02:30.708
Hold on to me!

02:34.875 --> 02:35.792
Help me, for fuck's sake!

02:39.083 --> 02:40.875
Move it! Get up here!

02:42.042 --> 02:43.500
Move it!

02:50.958 --> 02:54.000
The wire's tangled!
Try to cut it right there!

02:54.125 --> 02:56.417
I'll get hold here and cut through it.

02:59.167 --> 03:00.625
You can't be here!

03:01.083 --> 03:02.250
Go away!

03:05.875 --> 03:09.458
Don't shake the fence!
Don't shake the fucking fence!

03:14.500 --> 03:17.000
-Romeo 20 to COS.
<i>-This is COS, Romeo 20.</i>

03:17.125 --> 03:18.583
Requesting backup at Alpha 26.

03:18.708 --> 03:21.417
More migrants arriving from the shelter
to assist those crossing.

03:21.542 --> 03:22.583
Let me go!

03:47.750 --> 03:50.000
Just fucking stay still!

03:52.542 --> 03:53.708
Stop!

03:53.833 --> 03:54.958
Stop, stop!

03:55.042 --> 03:57.417
Just fucking stay still!

03:57.750 --> 03:59.167
Stop shaking the fence!

03:59.333 --> 04:00.708
Don't move...

04:17.541 --> 04:19.708
Miguel! Miguel, are you OK?

04:27.708 --> 04:29.125
He's not breathing.

04:47.708 --> 04:48.833
I'm OK.

04:50.167 --> 04:51.958
Call the COS! Call the COS!

05:11.500 --> 05:16.375
{\an8}DJA NATURE RESERVE
CAMEROON

06:14.542 --> 06:16.042
Jesus Christ!

06:24.958 --> 06:26.708
Look out for the bumps!

06:32.458 --> 06:33.750
It's my turn.

06:33.875 --> 06:35.917
It's late, mama will be angry.

06:36.000 --> 06:38.250
You promised, Ali!

06:38.875 --> 06:40.083
You promised.

10:09.708 --> 10:13.708
{\an8}MBOUMÁ
CAMEROON

10:30.500 --> 10:32.458
You're going to tell Kato.

10:33.417 --> 10:35.875
How will I get to Avebe now?

10:39.500 --> 10:40.750
It's all your fault.

10:40.875 --> 10:42.083
It's not my fault.

10:42.250 --> 10:44.875
-I didn't want to go there.
-Adu is six.

10:44.958 --> 10:47.000
He does what you say.
You're the oldest.

10:47.125 --> 10:49.958
But you asked me
to teach him to ride a bicycle.

10:50.042 --> 10:51.083
In the village.

10:51.208 --> 10:52.667
Not on those tracks.

10:57.167 --> 10:58.917
It was Kimba.

11:01.750 --> 11:05.792
-What?
-The elephant they killed was Kimba.

11:14.542 --> 11:17.250
It was probably recorded
by an immigrant from the shelter.

11:19.333 --> 11:21.917
-Is that all it shows?
-It's been up a few days.

11:23.125 --> 11:25.542
The Refugee Aid people
have made a complaint.

11:26.333 --> 11:27.583
Fucking great.

11:27.708 --> 11:30.375
It's to force the judge to request
access to the fence cameras.

11:31.250 --> 11:33.042
What can you see
from the fence cameras?

11:33.792 --> 11:35.458
Nothing. You can't see anything.

11:35.583 --> 11:37.542
We tried to get him down, end of story.

11:38.000 --> 11:39.708
Will we have to go to court?

11:39.833 --> 11:43.125
First thing we do
is talk to the chief, but it's OK.

11:43.500 --> 11:44.917
Because what happened...

11:45.000 --> 11:46.250
is what the report says.

11:46.417 --> 11:48.917
He died because of a fall, end of story.

11:49.375 --> 11:51.000
You're sure there are no more videos?

11:51.667 --> 11:52.958
What videos?

11:54.750 --> 11:56.917
You're pushing that defence hard.

11:57.042 --> 11:58.708
What defence, Mateo?

12:39.625 --> 12:40.792
Adu.

12:41.250 --> 12:42.417
Adu...

12:43.042 --> 12:44.583
Come here!

12:57.375 --> 12:58.375
Come.

13:12.375 --> 13:13.375
Come.

13:21.208 --> 13:22.542
Sit here.

13:29.875 --> 13:31.375
Come closer.

13:34.833 --> 13:35.917
Adu...

13:36.917 --> 13:39.792
You know I'm a friend
of your father's, don't you?

13:39.917 --> 13:41.750
Yes, Monsieur Neko.

13:42.375 --> 13:44.583
I take care of your family.

13:45.250 --> 13:48.208
Who found the water cans
for your mother?

13:48.750 --> 13:50.667
You did, Monsieur Neko.

13:50.958 --> 13:53.917
I have a friend in Mengueme
who needs a good bike

13:54.000 --> 13:56.292
to carry his cassava to market.

13:56.667 --> 13:59.792
I thought of your bike,
the one that belongs to Kato.

13:59.917 --> 14:02.292
My friend will pay a good price for it.

14:06.833 --> 14:07.875
No.

14:08.042 --> 14:09.208
No, what?

14:09.958 --> 14:11.667
Is something wrong?

14:15.542 --> 14:17.250
I lost it.

14:17.458 --> 14:18.917
What happened, Adu?

14:19.125 --> 14:20.625
You can tell me.

14:46.417 --> 14:47.250
Yes?

14:47.417 --> 14:48.417
What is it?

14:50.333 --> 14:51.333
What?

14:52.167 --> 14:54.500
No, I'll go to Yaoundé to pick her up.

14:55.000 --> 14:56.583
Yes, at the airport.

14:56.708 --> 14:58.750
No, no taxis, she can wait for me.

15:02.750 --> 15:04.708
Did she get her vaccinations?

15:05.417 --> 15:06.917
Her vaccinations.

15:08.333 --> 15:09.708
Did you ask her?

15:11.083 --> 15:13.375
I know she's not 12,
but she might as well be.

15:14.792 --> 15:15.792
OK.

15:16.042 --> 15:17.958
OK. Bye.

17:51.875 --> 17:52.750
Leave him.

17:54.375 --> 17:55.750
Let him go.

19:22.625 --> 19:24.500
Run! Run!

19:26.375 --> 19:27.667
Watch out!

21:38.125 --> 21:40.333
Will mama be OK?

21:40.458 --> 21:42.042
I don't want to talk about that.

21:42.167 --> 21:43.625
Why not?

21:44.167 --> 21:46.583
Thinking about mama
won't help us now.

21:46.708 --> 21:48.208
What are we going to do?

21:49.250 --> 21:51.292
We'll go to Aunt Leke's.

21:51.542 --> 21:53.625
She'll help us call dad.

21:54.542 --> 21:56.458
And take us to Spain.

22:24.292 --> 22:26.958
{\an8}YAOUNDÉ
CAMEROON

23:02.167 --> 23:04.667
Mum told me
they killed another elephant.

23:06.500 --> 23:09.458
And that if you used drones
you could track them better.

23:10.833 --> 23:12.292
Do you know how much a drone costs?

23:12.833 --> 23:15.250
-And how many we'd need?
-You're rich.

23:15.375 --> 23:16.625
Me, rich?

23:17.125 --> 23:18.583
Your granddad was a count!

23:19.542 --> 23:21.875
No, granddad married
the widow of a count.

23:22.250 --> 23:23.750
I have nothing to do with that.

23:24.125 --> 23:27.333
What you do have is a mega apartment
in Madrid, one in London,

23:27.458 --> 23:29.583
-a house in Morocco...
-Two ex-wives,

23:29.708 --> 23:31.750
a daughter
who can't stay out of trouble...

23:34.500 --> 23:37.375
You have 36,000 Twitter followers,
if you ask for one Euro...

23:37.500 --> 23:39.333
Since when do you care about elephants?

23:39.750 --> 23:41.375
No, Dad. I care about you.

23:41.500 --> 23:43.417
Well, if you care about me,

23:43.542 --> 23:46.292
try not to cause me any trouble
while you're here.

23:46.417 --> 23:47.708
I didn't ask to come.

23:47.875 --> 23:50.500
I was perfectly happy in Madrid.
I'd got a job.

23:51.042 --> 23:52.250
What kind of job?

23:52.375 --> 23:54.500
A job. At the amusement park.

23:54.958 --> 23:57.167
-At the amusement park...
-Yes.

23:59.250 --> 24:01.083
Do you want some advice?

24:01.500 --> 24:02.667
Please.

24:02.833 --> 24:04.958
Use this trip to make a change.

24:08.167 --> 24:09.417
OK.

24:22.958 --> 24:24.208
Ali.

24:25.208 --> 24:26.625
Ali, I'm thirsty.

24:27.708 --> 24:29.625
Five minutes to rest.

24:33.125 --> 24:34.083
Adu!

24:34.208 --> 24:36.125
Ali, please.

25:12.042 --> 25:13.333
Stop it!

25:14.083 --> 25:15.458
Ali, stop it.

25:56.167 --> 25:57.917
What would you have done?

25:59.500 --> 26:00.958
What would I have done?

26:01.125 --> 26:03.708
If I died, what would you do?

26:08.292 --> 26:09.750
Carry on.

27:53.083 --> 27:54.375
Adu, hurry up!

27:55.250 --> 27:56.917
Hurry up!

27:58.292 --> 28:01.208
-What?
-A truck stopped, let's go.

28:39.583 --> 28:41.375
Adu! Adu!

29:41.250 --> 29:42.333
Hello?

29:42.458 --> 29:43.500
Hi.

29:55.375 --> 29:59.750
This guy was just telling me
that the only sign of elephants he's seen

29:59.833 --> 30:01.750
is the shit they leave on the roads.

30:02.125 --> 30:03.125
What are you smoking?

30:03.292 --> 30:04.500
Tobacco.

30:04.625 --> 30:05.917
Tobacco?

30:07.125 --> 30:08.375
Smell it.

30:09.625 --> 30:11.958
This is not Spain.
You get 15 years for a joint.

30:12.042 --> 30:14.292
Dad, it's tobacco. I swear.

30:17.042 --> 30:19.500
-Whose is the bike?
-I found it in the jungle.

30:20.500 --> 30:21.583
I love it.

30:21.708 --> 30:23.500
-Can I keep it?
-What for?

30:23.625 --> 30:25.375
I don't know, a souvenir of Africa.

30:28.667 --> 30:32.083
Make a 50 Euro donation
to the Du Dja reserve and it's yours.

30:32.208 --> 30:33.375
50 Euros?

30:33.458 --> 30:35.542
That's what a gram of coke
costs in Madrid, right?

30:38.292 --> 30:40.375
You have no fucking clue, dad!

30:40.500 --> 30:42.500
Look, if you're angry
take a diazepam.

30:42.958 --> 30:44.417
Do I look angry to you?

30:44.542 --> 30:46.708
-I don't know.
-Come on, let's go.

30:49.250 --> 30:50.375
Very nice.

31:19.375 --> 31:21.375
They're practically identical.

31:22.500 --> 31:24.500
-I'm sorry?
-The statements.

31:24.625 --> 31:26.292
Yours and the corporal's.

31:27.375 --> 31:28.833
That's what happened.

31:29.958 --> 31:32.833
When they storm the fence,
it's always a mess.

31:32.958 --> 31:34.208
Yes, sir.

31:35.542 --> 31:37.917
Lots of tension, lots of pressure.

31:38.542 --> 31:40.083
They teach you many things
at the academy.

31:40.208 --> 31:42.250
But not how to get people
off a fence.

31:42.375 --> 31:43.333
No, sir.

31:44.917 --> 31:48.750
Last night they threw quicklime
at four officers.

31:48.917 --> 31:50.667
I know, sir.

31:51.458 --> 31:52.708
Did they throw some at you?

31:53.208 --> 31:54.625
No, sir.

31:56.667 --> 31:57.917
What's your name?

31:58.000 --> 32:00.375
Mateo, sir.

32:02.125 --> 32:06.417
There are a lot people here
who'd love to show us up.

32:06.500 --> 32:08.667
Who don't understand what we do here.

32:08.833 --> 32:10.792
People looking for minor details,

32:11.375 --> 32:13.125
mistakes, to attack us.

32:18.917 --> 32:21.667
Do you know what I'm getting at, Mateo?

32:25.917 --> 32:28.125
There were only three of us, sir.
We did all we could.

32:28.250 --> 32:29.875
That's not what I'm asking you.

32:34.417 --> 32:36.917
There was no mistake, sir.

33:35.042 --> 33:37.167
They can't take all that stuff.

33:37.917 --> 33:39.375
The truck is full.

33:39.625 --> 33:41.917
If everyone brought a bag,
we wouldn't fit.

33:42.042 --> 33:43.958
Their father told me...

33:44.125 --> 33:45.958
Their father is in Spain.

33:46.042 --> 33:47.792
We take care of things here.

33:48.250 --> 33:50.083
One bag is enough
for the two of them.

33:53.917 --> 33:57.500
Don't forget, they'll let you call
once a week.

33:57.625 --> 34:02.042
Don't lose your father's number,
and take care of your brother.

35:18.292 --> 35:19.917
Shit! Shit!

35:23.417 --> 35:25.333
What's the police doing to that man?

35:26.958 --> 35:28.250
What is it?

35:44.750 --> 35:45.750
Shit!

35:50.667 --> 35:52.625
Change of plans.

35:52.750 --> 35:55.083
-What?
-You're going to Paris, by plane.

35:55.667 --> 35:59.042
-What do you mean by plane?
-You're in luck.

36:20.958 --> 36:22.958
You have to climb up the wheels, quick.

36:23.125 --> 36:24.458
The wheels?

36:24.583 --> 36:26.958
They're full of cables
you can hang on to.

36:27.083 --> 36:28.125
When you get up there

36:28.208 --> 36:30.333
look for the duct
that leads to the dog area.

36:30.500 --> 36:31.917
What dogs?

36:32.042 --> 36:35.500
Europeans fly with their dogs
but they put them below.

36:36.083 --> 36:38.208
-Is it safe?
-Super safe.

36:45.250 --> 36:50.167
You have to wrap up.
It's very cold in the air.

36:53.917 --> 36:55.458
It's this or nothing.

36:58.042 --> 37:00.083
-My father paid...
-To take you to Morocco!

37:00.250 --> 37:03.917
And we're taking you to Paris!
We're doing you a favour!

37:05.208 --> 37:06.542
Don't you want to go?

37:06.667 --> 37:09.833
Then stay here. This is all I can do.

37:14.958 --> 37:18.208
Pick a really big one.
They leave every evening.

37:18.333 --> 37:20.375
That's the one that goes to Paris.

37:25.958 --> 37:27.500
Good luck!

37:45.333 --> 37:46.958
What's wrong?

37:47.125 --> 37:48.958
I don't want to go in there.

37:49.083 --> 37:50.875
Why not? It's just noise.

37:50.958 --> 37:52.500
No, it's not just the noise.

37:54.292 --> 37:55.625
What do you want to do?

37:56.375 --> 37:57.958
I don't know.

38:00.333 --> 38:02.417
-What are you doing?
-I'm leaving.

38:03.125 --> 38:04.792
What are you going to do?

38:06.292 --> 38:07.833
Go back to the village?

38:08.500 --> 38:09.583
No.

40:02.917 --> 40:04.667
What's happening?

41:31.500 --> 41:33.375
Ali, I'm cold!

41:33.750 --> 41:35.583
Let's put on the clothes.

41:41.375 --> 41:42.833
Quick!

41:44.167 --> 41:45.875
Here, take it.

42:05.042 --> 42:06.958
I'm still cold.

42:10.792 --> 42:12.375
Don't worry, Adu.

42:23.333 --> 42:26.375
Let's sit together,
that will keep us warm.

42:46.792 --> 42:49.083
How long is the journey?

42:49.208 --> 42:50.375
Not long.

44:01.917 --> 44:03.083
Ali.

44:07.833 --> 44:09.875
Ali, wake up!

44:21.792 --> 44:23.625
Ali, wake up!

44:29.875 --> 44:32.875
Alika, wake up! Alika!

45:52.500 --> 45:54.833
Hey, what are you doing here?

45:55.958 --> 45:59.208
What are you doing here?
It's a forbidden zone.

46:00.625 --> 46:03.417
Don't you know you can't be here?

46:26.583 --> 46:28.125
I'm going to bed.

46:34.458 --> 46:36.083
What's wrong with you?

46:36.208 --> 46:37.333
What?

46:37.458 --> 46:40.667
-What the hell's that doing there?
-Dad, it's fake.

46:41.250 --> 46:42.833
It's plastic. From the party.

46:42.958 --> 46:44.083
What party?

46:44.208 --> 46:46.333
A party here in the hotel.

46:46.667 --> 46:48.542
You have to integrate, right?

46:50.042 --> 46:51.375
Are you on something?

46:52.125 --> 46:54.125
-What do you mean?
-Your eyes are red.

46:54.292 --> 46:55.958
I've been up all night.

46:56.833 --> 47:00.083
Sandra, do you know where you are?
Or why they gave you that?

47:00.208 --> 47:02.833
Yes, dad. I also know I'm an adult.

47:02.958 --> 47:05.125
If you were,
I wouldn't have to chase after you.

47:05.250 --> 47:08.042
Chase after me? Since when?
3 months, 6 months ago?

47:08.125 --> 47:10.583
-Since you lost the plot!
-Because everything was fine before?

47:11.958 --> 47:14.500
While you're with me you're not going
to behave like you did with your mother.

47:14.583 --> 47:17.083
How you know what I did with her?
You weren't there!

47:34.667 --> 47:36.083
Mateo...

47:36.958 --> 47:39.708
Hi. I'm Paloma, I'm a lawyer
with the Commission for Refugee Aid.

47:40.250 --> 47:42.250
-Sorry, not today.
-It's about the Tatou case.

47:42.375 --> 47:44.375
Can we talk for a second?

47:44.500 --> 47:47.792
-I've already made a...
-Just 5 minutes. It's very important.

47:51.458 --> 47:52.958
What a lovely view.

47:54.167 --> 47:55.750
It was my grandfather's flat.

47:56.458 --> 47:58.208
-Are you from Melilla?
-No.

47:58.792 --> 48:01.042
I was born in Madrid,
but I'm from a military family.

48:01.167 --> 48:02.542
-So am I.
-Really?

48:03.417 --> 48:05.292
I have many friends
in the Guardia Civil.

48:10.292 --> 48:13.917
Look, Mateo, I'm not here
to ruin anyone's career.

48:14.042 --> 48:16.208
I know you're under huge pressure.

48:16.333 --> 48:18.417
You said 5 minutes, didn't you?

48:20.958 --> 48:24.083
We've found the immigrants
who were with Tatou on the fence.

48:25.375 --> 48:28.792
They say you guys
hit him over the head with a baton.

48:30.375 --> 48:32.667
Did they say that
Tatou kicked my chief in the head

48:32.833 --> 48:34.042
and almost killed him?

48:34.167 --> 48:37.333
Are you saying your corporal
was justified in doing what he did?

48:37.958 --> 48:40.875
I'm not justifying anything. It's a fact.

48:40.958 --> 48:43.625
Tatou is dead, that's also a fact.

48:44.042 --> 48:46.458
You know they've started
throwing quicklime at us?

48:46.583 --> 48:48.750
Blood, faeces..

48:49.792 --> 48:52.125
Sometimes it's three of us
holding back 100.

48:52.208 --> 48:53.417
Of course I know that.

48:53.875 --> 48:56.917
Many of your fellow officers
have asked me to talk to the press.

48:57.042 --> 48:58.792
-And I've done it.
-No one cares.

48:58.917 --> 49:00.833
-The headline is Tatou.
-You're wrong.

49:00.958 --> 49:02.250
The headline isn't Tatou.

49:02.375 --> 49:04.833
The headline is that
those who should uphold the law

49:04.958 --> 49:06.125
ended up killing an immigrant.

49:06.250 --> 49:08.917
-We didn't kill anyone.
-Are you sure, Mateo?

49:20.083 --> 49:23.083
We're bringing Tatou's friends in
to make a statement.

49:23.208 --> 49:24.458
I've told the truth.

49:28.667 --> 49:29.583
Mateo...

49:30.792 --> 49:32.458
Ask yourself one question:

49:33.292 --> 49:34.833
Do you want it to happen again?

51:24.083 --> 51:25.417
How do you do that?

51:26.500 --> 51:28.500
How do you do that with the balls?

51:30.708 --> 51:31.792
Magic?

51:45.542 --> 51:46.500
Adu.

51:54.792 --> 51:55.875
Illegal?

52:13.667 --> 52:16.125
I came here in there.

52:16.250 --> 52:17.417
In the wheel.

52:27.458 --> 52:28.417
"Alone"?

52:28.542 --> 52:30.917
No, with my sister.

52:31.375 --> 52:32.833
Alika.

54:15.458 --> 54:16.667
Can you run?

54:58.500 --> 54:59.958
Come here.

56:26.667 --> 56:27.958
Carmen...

56:30.250 --> 56:31.542
-How are things?
-How are you?

56:31.667 --> 56:32.625
Good.

56:32.792 --> 56:34.208
This is my daughter, Sandra.

56:34.333 --> 56:35.333
Hi.

56:35.875 --> 56:36.875
Nice to meet you.

56:38.583 --> 56:39.833
Your dad talks a lot about you.

56:39.958 --> 56:40.875
Really?

56:40.958 --> 56:42.708
Yes, good things.

56:43.417 --> 56:45.083
Right, Carmen?

56:46.292 --> 56:48.208
I have things to do.
I'll be back in 2 hours.

56:48.333 --> 56:50.125
-You won't have a coffee?
-No, when I get back.

56:50.500 --> 56:53.625
You listen to Carmen.
She's the cleverest woman I know.

56:59.292 --> 57:01.625
Which arm will you do the jab in,
left or right?

57:02.167 --> 57:03.875
No, first we're going to talk.

57:04.542 --> 57:06.042
-OK.
-Would you like a coffee?

57:06.500 --> 57:09.208
